2 Preamble
3 WHEREAS, Thomas V. Mike Miller, Jr. served in the House of Delegates from 1971
4 to 1975 and in the Senate from 1975 to 2020; and
5 WHEREAS, Thomas V. Mike Miller, Jr. was the longest serving State Senate
6 President in America’s history, having served as Maryland Senate President from 1987 to
7 2020 during his 49 years of service in the General Assembly; and
8 WHEREAS, Thomas V. Mike Miller, Jr. worked in a bipartisan manner to pass
9 meaningful legislation; and
10 WHEREAS, Thomas V. Mike Miller, Jr. had a passion for the Chesapeake Bay and
11 for education, and was active with the Chesapeake Bay Trust family since 1985 when it
12 was established by the Maryland General Assembly to engage people in the protection and
13 restoration of natural resources; and
14 WHEREAS, Chapters 257 and 276 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2010,
15 sponsored by Thomas V. Mike Miller, Jr., established the Chesapeake Conservation Corps
16 Program and directed the Chesapeake Bay Trust to administer the Program; and
17 WHEREAS, To continue the memory and honor of Thomas V. Mike Miller, Jr. and
18 his positive influence on the Chesapeake Bay; now, therefore,
19 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
20 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
